<TITLE> 2 more kidnapped in Bandarban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, Aug 07 (bdnews24.com)Criminals on Friday abducted two construction workers, the district intelligence officer said. Mohammad Yusuf, 35, who is from Sonagazi Upazila in Feni, and Mohammad Rabiul, 22, from Lalmonirhat,were kidnapped at 3pm when they were overseeing construction of Gherao-Roagchhari Road under CHT Development Project, Mohammad Rokon said. Officer in charge at Roangchhari Police Station 'Mohiuddin' said they started a rescue operation. Mahbubur Rahman and Amal Das were the partners of the construction firm, MM Traders, that had been tasked with constructing the road. On the kidnapping incident, Das said none contacted them to demand ransom. On Tuesday, criminals had kidnapped a fish farmer, Mohammed Faruq, from Chhaingya Danesh Parah of Roangchhari Upazila in Bandarban. His family members ransomed him the following day. bdn
